  "text": "Cell Culture. Human embryonic kidney (HEK293) cells (ATCC CRL-3216) were maintained in Earl's MEM (Sigma-Aldrich), CHO-K1 cells were cultured in Ham's F-12 medium (Sigma-Aldrich), and HT22 cells were maintained in DMEM (Sigma-Aldrich) with 100 units/mL penicillin and 100 μg/mL streptomycin supplemented with 10% (vol/vol) FCS (Gibco) and 2 mM glutamine. HKC8 cells, a human-derived renal proximal tubule cell line [CITATION_1] , were cultured in DMEM/Ham's F-12 medium 1:1 mixture supplemented with 2.5% FCS, insulin-transferrin-selenium supplement (Gibco), and 2 mM glutamine. All cells were held at 37°C in a humified atmosphere with 5% CO 2 . CHO-K1 cells stably expressing human NHERF1 {SLC9A3R1 [solute carrier family 9, subfamily A (NHE3, cation proton antiporter 3), member 3 regulator 1], NG_013022} were cultured in Ham's F-12 medium additionally containing 800 μg·ml −1 G418 (Invitrogen).",
